data.name: radManual.Text
data.value: Manually approve applicable Encompass service packs and critical patches before they are applied* (see note above). Use the Send to Testing and Manage Test Users buttons to evaluate a selected service pack or critical patch prior to approval.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
Encompass service packs are monthly planned maintenance releases. A critical patch is an update that is necessary to address a critical defect and/or compliance change. Typically these types of updates are applied to your users’ computers automatically. If preferred, you can choose to manually approve each applicable service pack and critical patch before it is applied.* If you select the manual option, you must return to this screen to review and approve new service pack and critical patch updates.
* Certain service pack and critical patch releases are always applied to your users’ computers automatically and cannot be controlled manually. Typically these releases include critical compliance or feature updates, or changes to the Encompass Server that result in a new Encompass version number.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Major upgrades occur less frequently and introduce significant new features and enhancements. These upgrades must first be downloaded and applied to your Encompass Server. Your users' computers will be upgraded when they first log in to the updated Encompass Server.
